collections data types
-----------------------
- data types which allow us to store multiple values into a single variable

- 4 collection data types - list, tuple, set & dictionary


List - []
-----
- mutable
- can be updated and modified.
- ordered, indexed
- duplicates are accepted
- ordered - elements are stored in the same given order

tuple - ()
-----
- immutable
- cannot update/modify
- ordered, indexed
- duplicates are accepted
- ordered - elements are stored in the same given order

Set - {}
--------
- mutable - we can update and modify the elements in a set
- unordered, un-indexed, un-duplicated
- duplicates are ignored
- unordered - elements are stored in random order



